readability_reflection: Concatenation was most easier because I am used to it. However, interpolation seems like it would make for more readable code in the more meaningful context. What I mean is it was hard to read concatenation when it was just seemingly random letters/numbers, but when it was within the URLs it made a lot more sense (and wasn't separated out by " + ")
comprehension_debugging: I don't exactly know how concatenation works with spaces and/or multiple variables inside the brackets, so that was pretty confusing. Concatenation for the most part always is clear in this respect.
preference_rationale: I want to get more familiar with interpolation in order to not have all of my outputs be separated by addition symbols. There aren't many other factors affecting my decision.
learning_curve: I was used to concatenation but not interpolation so I was second guessing on some questions with interpolation.
